---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../../config/site";
---

<MainLayout title="Add-on Support">
  <article class="panel policy">
    <h1>Crystord Add-on Support</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: September 15, 2025</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>Welcome to the Crystord Add-on support page. Here you'll find resources to help you get
      started, answers to common questions, troubleshooting steps, and ways to contact us.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <h3>What is Crystord?</h3>
      <p>Crystord is a Google Workspace Add-on that syncs variables between Google Sheets™ and
      Google Slides™. Use it to create dynamic slide templates where placeholders like
      <code>&#123;&#123;variable_name&#125;&#125;</code> are replaced with values from your
      spreadsheet.</p>

      <h3>Basic Setup</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Install the Crystord Add-on from the
        <a href={siteConfig.addonMarketplaceUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Workspace Marketplace</a>.</li>
        <li>Open your Slides™ presentation and add your variables in any part of your slides as
        <code>&#123;&#123;variable_name&#125;&#125;</code>.</li>
        <li>Click the bottom-left expansion arrow and press the Crystord icon to open the sidebar.</li>
        <li>The sidebar displays four buttons:
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Create Database:</strong> Creates a new Sheets™ file named "database" that
            the Crystord Add-on is allowed to read, and opens it in a new tab. This file is
            automatically selected and initially empty. Add your variables by filling the table with
            the columns "Name" and "Value".</li>
            <li><strong>Select Database:</strong> Allows you to select a previously created Sheets™
            file (database).</li>
            <li><strong>Open Database:</strong> Opens the selected database in a new tab.</li>
            <li><strong>Synchronise:</strong> Updates your current Slides™ file with the latest
            values from the selected database.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>The first step is to create a database — nothing works without it. After making any
        changes to the database, always click "Synchronise" to reflect updates in your Slides.
        Use clear and consistent naming conventions for variables to avoid conflicts during
        synchronisation.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>How do I install the Add-on?</h3>
      <p>Install directly via the
      <a href={siteConfig.addonMarketplaceUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Workspace Marketplace</a>
      or from within Google Slides™ by opening the side panel and searching for "Crystord".</p>

      <h3>The variables in Slides aren't updating.</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Ensure you have created and selected a database using the "Create Database" or
        "Select Database" buttons in the sidebar.</li>
        <li>Double-check that the variable names in your Slides match exactly with the names in
        the database (case-sensitive, no extra spaces).</li>
        <li>Click the "Synchronise" button in the sidebar to update Slides with the latest values
        from the database.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Do I need to re-link the Sheet every time?</h3>
      <p>No. Once a database is created or selected, it remains linked to the current Slides file.
      You can refresh values as often as needed.</p>

      <h3>What format should I use for variables in Slides?</h3>
      <p>Use curly brackets: <code>&#123;&#123;variable_name&#125;&#125;</code>
      (e.g., <code>&#123;&#123;item_name&#125;&#125;</code>).</p>

      <h3>What if I accidentally delete the database file?</h3>
      <p>If the database file is deleted, create a new one using the "Create Database" button in
      the sidebar and re-add your variables. The database file is a normal Sheets file — you can
      also try to recover it from the Google Drive trash.</p>

      <h3>What if I select the wrong database?</h3>
      <p>Use the "Select Database" button in the sidebar to choose the correct one. Ensure the
      correct database is selected before clicking "Synchronise".</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

      <h3>Add-on not appearing?</h3>
      <p>Refresh Google Slides™ and ensure you are using the same account you installed the Add-on
      with.</p>

      <h3>Sidebar won't open or is unresponsive?</h3>
      <p>Try closing and reopening Google Slides™, or reinstall the Add-on if needed.</p>

      <h3>Unexpected errors or bugs?</h3>
      <p>Take a screenshot or copy the error message and contact support (details below).</p>

      <h3>Is the Add-on up to date?</h3>
      <p>Ensure you are using the latest version of the Crystord Add-on. Outdated versions may not
      support the latest features or workflows. Update via the Google Workspace Marketplace if
      needed.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact &amp; Feedback</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact us at:</strong>
        <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a></li>
        <li><strong>Bug reports:</strong> Please provide the error message, browser version, and a
        description of what you were doing when the issue occurred.</li>
        <li><strong>Feature suggestions:</strong> We welcome your ideas — email us at the address
        above.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href={siteConfig.addonMarketplaceUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Crystord on
        Google Workspace Marketplace</a></li>
        <li><a href={siteConfig.youtubeUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Crystord on YouTube</a>
        — tutorials and feature walkthroughs</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p class="trademark">
      <a href="/google-addon">Google Add-on</a>
      &nbsp;·&nbsp;
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
      &nbsp;·&nbsp;
      <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>
      <br />
      <small>Google Sheets™ and Google Slides™ are trademarks of Google LLC.</small>
    </p>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .policy section {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .policy h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .policy h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--brand-dark);
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .policy ul,
  .policy ol {
    padding-left: 1.4rem;
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.8rem;
  }

  .policy li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  code {
    font-family: monospace;
    background: var(--surface-alt);
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .meta {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .trademark {
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .trademark a {
    color: var(--muted);
  }
</style>
